  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The objective was to evaluate perioperative morbidity after head and neck microsurgical
      reconstruction.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The objective was to evaluate perioperative morbidity after head and neck microsurgical
      reconstruction. A retrospective chart review of all patients undergoing head and neck free
      flap reconstruction was conducted and the overall hospital length of stay and the incidence
      of perioperative medical and surgical complications were assessed.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
